  "texts": [
    "Unlike the AGI and ANI approaches, the current development of LLMs' moral With the lack of self-reflective capabilities, LLMs have yet to attain the character stage as envisioned by Dewey, thereby preventing them from having moral competence equivalent to that of humans.",
    "Hence, as discussed in section \"Limitations and challenges of LLMs' moral competence\", various ethical issues and unpredictable risks are still there, particularly those associated with potential manipulation and inducement, which cannot be addressed solely through RLHF.",
    "A comprehensive approach to the formation and governance of LLMs' moral competence remains essential, indicating opportunities for future work across various dimensions.",
    "Enhancing the capabilities of RLHF or RLAIF -as recently developed by Anthropic (Bai et al., 2022) -remains important; further, external societal governance and legal regulation are also significant.",
    "Addressing these complexities requires continual interdisciplinary investigation and research."
  ]
}